Frontend Flow: 
app/ (Page) → Loads components/ (Lego Blocks) → Runs lib/ (To talk to Backend)

Frontend Components:
1. app/
- the map of the frontend 
    - [twin: routes in backend]
- name = URL 
    - (e.g., folder about/ = website.com/about)
- subcategories: 
    a. page.tsx 
        - actual webpage shown for that URL.
        - should start with: import { projectname } from "@/filename/projectname";
    b. layout.tsx 
        - skeleton of the website (the <head> and <body> tags where the pages go).
    c. globals.css
        - layout design

2. components/
- whats inside the page
- reusable code [note: Hero in line 2 and 9 of page]

3. lib/ (or utils/)
- contains the functions where you write code to fetch data from your Express backend.

4. tailwind.config.ts / next.config.ts
simply the setup configuration for the visual design (Tailwind) and the frontend engine (Next.js).

5. .next/
the compiled output folder Next.js builds automatically.
completely ignore this folder!

6. package.json
labels everything installed (React, Next.js, styling packages).
Does that help clear up the puzzle pieces of the frontend?


